commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented DateRange, DateInterval enum and tests
commitResults.messageBody:
DateRange represents a range of dates from start date to end date, and
can split itself into smaller date ranges representing days, weeks,
months and years, using the DateInterval enum.

ExpenseTimeline encapsulates the aggregate expenses per interval of
time, over a specified range of time. Also imported hamcrest, to aid
with writing understandable tests.

commitResults.messageBody:
Expense display only switches between default view and archive view
when a command that affects either is made. Commands that do not
affect them will cause the displayed list to remain the same.

Commands that switch the view include:
* Add
* Edit
* Delete
* Clear
* Find
* List
* All archive commands besides ListArchiveNames
* All tag commands besides ListTag
* Undo
* Redo

Commands that do not switch the view include:
* Exit
* Help
* ListArchiveNames
* ListTag
* History
* DisplayStats
